Standardized domains and service 
domains, that align with business 
areas, allowing for a consistent way 
for channels to integrate into the 
Banks' systems, hiding the 
complexities of system APIs / logic


Enterprise Middleware:

•Exposes canonical data models and common capabilities
•Enables observability, auditability, and reuse measurement
•Performs cross-domain integration and orchestration
•Remains consumer and system (backend / frontend) agnostic
•Adheres to the highest level of guidelines
•Operates as the preferred integration point across banks



Enterprise Middleware Does Not:

•Retain long term, persistent enterprise data
•Have multiple representations of the same domain and data
•Align to a specific system
•Modify or alter behavior per consumer



System

Core and system-specific services 
that handle read and writes from / 
to Systems of Record (SORs) and 
any system specific logic


System Middleware:

•Exposes core / vendor systems of record (SORs) data and 
functions
•Handles authentication and authorization to core systems
•Provides stable and reusable services toread and write data 
from / toSORs 
•Implements system-specific logic



System Middleware Does Not:

•Bypass enterprise security or governance standards
•Store or transform data beyond integration needs
•Aggregate or orchestrate actions across multiple systems
•Implement business or process logic
•Serve channel-specific needs





