1.2 Target State Operating Model: Organizational Structure


To achieve the target state and enable the enterprise middleware layer to operate effectively, each layer must be accountable for distinct responsibilities, standards, and 
outcomes, with the Enterprise Layer team driving cross-domain integrations and governance.


Experience Layer

•Owned by federated business or product teams 
•Continue to build APIs with support from API enablement teams when 
needed
•Curates andtailorsdatafrom the enterprise layer into the format and type 
needed for each channel, and adds channel-specific logic
•Prioritizes agility and rapid product delivery to end consumers



New – Enterprise Layer

•Centralized ownership through Enterprise Middleware Team
•Defines and creates domains and service domains
•Responsibilities:
•Own and create enterprise APIs
•Define standards for cross-domain orchestration, and business 
process orchestration that span multiple systems






System Layer

•Owned by federated Systems of Record (SORs) or system teams (e.g. 
core, ERP, CRM, GL, HR)
•Provides system APIs and integration services
•Focused on reliability, security, and data integrity
•Accessed directly by enterprise layer services
•lightweight orchestration only when atomic transactions are unavailable, and 
limit it to within the bounded context of the core



